FBIS4-36449 "drnes111_k_94012" FBIS-NES-94-111 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 IRAQ Allied Use of Arab Facilities Protested Allied Use of Arab Facilities Protested Arab League Informed of `Violations' JN0606115794 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1025 GMT 6 Jun 94 JN0606115794 Baghdad INA Arabic BFN [Text] Cairo, 6 Jun (INA) -- Iraq has protested to the Arab League General Secretariat against the continued facilities provided by the rulers of Saudi Arabia and Kuwait to U.S., British, and French aircraft violating Iraq's airspace, noting that this poses a serious threat to Iraq's security and sovereignty. In a letter addressed to Arab League Secretary General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid, Iraq's permanent representative said these aircraft continued their violation of Iraqi airspace during the period 24-31 May. They carried out 352 sorties flying from their bases in Saudi Arabia and Kuwait. Iraq's representative asked that the letter be circulated, along with a list detailing the violations, to the Arab member states to acquaint them with these regrettable facts.
